2) Explain about Method Overloading and Method Overriding concept with example program
Method Overloading: 
•	Same method name but different parameters (type/number/order) in the same class; happens at compile time.
•	Overloading improves readability.
Program:
package pratsoops;
class Overload{
void calculate (int a,int b) { //parameters
	int e = a+b;
	System.out.println("Add a & b :"+e);
}
void Loc (String world1,String word2) { //parameters
	String g = world1+ word2;
	System.out.println("Joining two Strings:"+g);
 }
}
public class Overloadingoops {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
	Overload Val = new Overload();
	Val.calculate(6,6);
         Overload Location = new Overload();
	Val.Loc(" I am From "," Kodungaiyur");

	}

}

Method Overriding:
•	A subclass provides a new version of a method already defined in its parent class with the same signature; happens at runtime.
•	while overriding enables runtime behaviour changes.
Program:
package pratsoops;
class Animal {
    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Animal makes sound");
    }
}

class Cat extends Animal {
    @Override
    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Cat sounds:");
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Animal Cats = new Cat ();  // parent reference, child object
        Cats.sound();             // calls Cat’s method
    }
}







